#import "/formatting.typ": *

#show: recipe.with(title: "Bean Soup, Vegan", panel-width: 38%)[
  *Pre-Broth*
  - 115g celery #aside[1 cup]
  - 900g dried beans #aside[1 packet]

  *Broth*
  - 2L water
  - 125g soy sauce #aside[1/2 cup]
  - 40g avocado oil #aside[3 tbsp.]
  - 480g tomatoes, blended #aside[2 large]
  - 350g onions, diced #aside[2 medium]
  - 160g bell peppers, diced
  - 30g salt #aside[2 tbsp.]
  - 15g vegetable seasoning, unsalted
  - 12g seaweed, dry, crushed
  - 10g yeast flakes
  - 3 bay leaves
  - 1 pinch cumin

  #sb[Afterwards]
  - Ghost pepper (optional)#footnote[~Because capsaicin has a relatively low sublimation
      point, we introduce this at the very end.
    ]

  - Cilantro, diced, to taste

  *Yields many servings.*
]

*The Day Before:*
- If beans are dry:
  + Rinse beans in cold water.
  + Add beans to large pot. Soak in water for at least 8 hours.
  + Repeat rinse.

- If celery is *NOT* dry:
  + Leave celery in food dehydrator.

*The Night Before:*
+ Add beans, ample water, and broth ingredients to crock-pot.
+ Set crock-pot to Low.
+ Shuffle celery in dehydrator, if applicable.
+ Go to bed, 8-10 hours.

*The Day Of*

+ Set crock-pot to Warm.
+ Cut & crush celery.
+ Mix celery & hot peppers into soup.

Serve hot with cilantro. Good with tortillas or other carbs.

== Trivia

This recipe was modeled off of @R_bean-soup-rice-cooker[my earlier bean soup recipe], in
haste for a potluck on 18 Apr. 2026. This is perhaps most obvious in how much I go out of
my way to inject umami (soy sauce, celery, tomatoes, seaweed), since I normally expect it
to come free with the meat in my bean soup. The only reason it's vegan is so that I can
give it to some Seventh-Day Adventists, and the only reason it calls for a crock-pot is so
that I can go to bed soon.
